TWENTY-FOURTH NORTHERN MARIANAS COMMONWEALTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SPECIAL SESSION, 2025 S.R. NO. 24-04
A SENATE RESOLUTION
To call for Taiwan’s inclusion in the World Health
Assembly (WHA), the International Police Criminal
Organization (INTERPOL), the International Civil Aviation
Organization (ICAO), and the United Nations Framework
Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC).
1 WHEREAS, since 1911, Taiwan has evolved into a vital model of democracy,
2 prosperity, and innovation, demonstrating its commitment to the well-being of its people
3 and its capacity to contribute to the global community; and
4 WHEREAS, the enactments of the Taiwan Relations Act in 1979, the Asia
5 Reassurance Initiative Act of 2018, the Taiwan Travel Act of 2018, and the Taiwan Allies
6 International Protection and Enhancement Initiative (TAIPEI) Act of 2019; have fostered
7 significant and enduring cooperation between the United States and Taiwan, including the
8 Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI) in Political Union with the
9 United States, strengthening our bilateral relationship and recognizing Taiwan's strategic
10 importance in the Indo-Pacific region by facilitating continued cooperation on security,
11 economic development, health, and democratic governance; and
12 WHEREAS, Taiwan has consistently demonstrated its commitment to the stability
13 and economic prosperity of the United States and its allies in the Indo-Pacific through
14 initiatives such as the Indo-Pacific Economic Framework (IPEF); and
15 WHEREAS, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI), a U.S.
16 territory, shares deep and enduring historical and cultural ties with Taiwan, rooted in a
17 shared history of maritime connection that has profoundly influenced our languages,
18 cultures, and ways of life; and
19 WHEREAS, the sister city relationship established in 2007 between the
20 Municipality of Saipan and the city of Hualien further solidifies the bond between the
21 CNMI and Taiwan, fostering cooperation across various sectors to promote mutual
22 understanding and collaboration; and

