1 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, that the Senate of the Twenty-Fourth
2 Northern Marianas Commonwealth Legislature hereby joins the people of the
3 Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands in urging Taiwan’s inclusion in the World
4 Health Assembly (WHA), the International Police Criminal Organization (INTERPOL),
5 the International Civil Aviation Organization (ICAO), and the United Nations Framework
6 Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC); and
7 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the President of the Senate shall certify and
8 the Senate Legislative Secretary shall attest to the adoption of this Resolution, and
9 thereafter the Senate Clerk shall transmit certified copies to Ms. Mary Lou Valdez, the
10 PAHO/WHO Deputy Director; Mary Rodriguez, INTERPOL Vice President, representing
11 the United States; Juan Carlos Salazar, ICAO Secretary General; Simon Stiell, UNCC
12 Executive Secretary; Honorable Arnold I. Palacios, Governor, Commonwealth of the
13 Northern Mariana Islands; the Honorable Kimberlyn King-Hinds, CNMI Delegate to the
14 House of Representatives, Washington, 119th United States Congress.
